   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya Drought 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There is a worsening food and nutrition situation in Kenya, attributed mainly to the poor performance of the OND 2020 and the MAM 2021
Projected 1,913,265 persons will need assistance (34% increase from the 1.4 million February 2021)
At least 12 Counties affected -&#xC2;&#xA0;Marsabit, Mandera, Garissa, Wajir, Kilifi, Tana River, Lamu, Samburu, Kitui, Lamu, Isiolo and Laikipia are in the alert drought phase
The worst affected counties-&#xC2;&#xA0; Turkana, Garissa, Wajir and Marsabit counties which have about 5% of their populations in IPC 4 (NDMA, July 2021).
&#xC2;</narrative>
  </description>
